{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSToolBarTop","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"The top toolbar (aka ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"navigation bar","type":"text"}]},{"text":" on iOS and iPadOS 18 and lower) sits at the top of the screen and provides contextual information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and controls related to the current view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It typically displays the page title, and may include navigation actions such as “Back” or “Close” as well as supplementary actions.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It can contains leading and trailing actions.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSToolBarTop","kind":"identifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"toolBarTop(_:hasLargeTitle:subtitle:leadingItems:trailingItems:)"},{"text":"  View helper applies a SwiftUI toolbar configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Appearances","text":"Appearances","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With Liquid Glass \/ iOS 26+ the OS will change the rendering of the toolbar items depending to the context:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The OS can group the items of same types in one group with kind of rectangle (e.g. views with menus)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But for buttons items they will remain isolated","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The placement of the title can be leading or centered depending to the length of the text","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The text can be truncated if there is not enough remaining space","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The OS can apply another style for the back button","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Without Liquid Glass \/ iOS 18 and lower, the OS won’t change that much the style of the toolbar items, Items won’t be visually grouped.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Globaly the appearence of the * navigation bar* elements is changed by the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsNavigationBarAppearance"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"helper of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"text":" that must be applyed on the root view of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationStack"},{"text":" for example.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Technical constraints","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Technical-constraints"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To be sure for iOS 18 and lower the back buttton and text have the good color, in your main view apply the following accent color:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["    struct AppMainView: View {","        var body: some View {","            ContentView()","                .accentColor(theme.colors.contentDefault)","        }","    }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Platform-considerations","text":"Platform considerations","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component is available on iOS, iPadOS, and visionOS","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component is not available for watchOS, 